# Hooks tracked in git are PROJECT hooks - they run for everyone who enables
# core.hooksPath (.githooks) on this repo.
#
# The entries below are installed LOCALLY by `graphify hook install` on a single
# machine. They are machine-specific (absolute interpreter paths, local cache
# locations) and must NOT be committed. Ignoring them here keeps `git status`
# clean and makes the project-vs-local split obvious at a glance: tracked file
# in this folder => project hook; ignored file => local-only hook.
/post-commit
/post-checkout
